  "claim_scope": "Exact integer dual certificates for the three source-151 row-6 label-4 assignment-0 endpoint rows left uncovered by the full-cone LP-screen diagnostic. The certificates prove infeasibility of the current normalized zero-sum and coordinatewise-nonpositive LP screens over the fixed natural-order Kalmanson/Altman row family. They are route-pruning evidence only: they do not prove the local quotients are geometrically realizable, do not prove assignments 0 or 11 are possible or impossible, do not prove support existence, center migration, row forcing, endpoint-8 forcing, n=9, the bootstrap bridge, or Erdos #97, and they are not a counterexample.",
